public int getRepResponseTimeMs()
Returns the average reponse time (aka ping time) of the Usbor's peer. This is the amount of time it takes a message to make a round trip, to the peer and back again.

Returns:
the average response time (in milliseconds) of the Usbor's peer

isGhost

public boolean isGhost()
Determines if the Usbor is a ghost.

An Usbor may become disconnected from its peer object in the Nexus. This could happen, for example, if the device is unplugged, the Nexus is shut down, or the Nexus connection is lost (network problems). In such a case, the Usbor dies and becomes a "ghost".

A ghost Usbor has the following properties:

  • It receives no new data from its Nexus-based peer object.
  • getXxx() methods still work, but the data will be stale and will no longer be updated.
  • The Usbor object will never come back to life. If the Usbor becomes accessible again later, a new Usbor object will be created.
  • All of its Pod's are also ghosts.

    • Returns:
    true if the Usbor has become a ghost; false otherwise
